{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Record_time</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"codex","href":"../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Record_time","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>A very simple benchmarking API.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value external anchored\" id=\"val-record_time\"><a href=\"#val-record_time\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> record_time : <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>By default OCaml uses floats to record dates, which makes me worry about precision. This simple C API does not have this defect. bench_return_time returns the number of microseconds since the last call to bench_record_time.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value external anchored\" id=\"val-return_time\"><a href=\"#val-return_time\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> return_time : <span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> int</span></code></div></div>"}